Reasoning: 
1. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) - The paper discusses the construction of a numeration system using finite automata, which is a topic closely related to formal languages and automata theory. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with the properties of regular languages and polynomials, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper uses logical reasoning to prove the main result and to establish the properties of the constructed language. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the density function of the regular language, which is a concept related to information theory. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the recognizability of polynomials by finite automata, which is a topic related to computational complexity.
